content.description: Sit start on jugs as per Grand Central, move onto crimps on left face, dyno to lip.
content.location: Boulder on right side of railroad cliff line.

content.description: Start low with good edge. Toss up and right to pinch snd balance up to slab face.
Climb up low angle slab using thin feet and good holds
content.location: Directly off the tracks below Pine Tree Step-across

content.description: Starting with left hand low and right up on good edge, crank up to sharp crimp and reach the drilled out hole. Top-out.
content.location: 10 feet up hill and behind Railroad Slab

content.description: Sit start and go straight up the arete.
content.location: Free standing boulder on right side of Railroad amphitheater.

content.description: Relatively vertical, splitter #5 crack in a right facing corner. Offwidth moves to an easier topout.
content.location: Take the southern approach to the top of Railroad Amphitheater. Approximately two-thirds of the way up, look for a tree leaning against the cliff band.

content.description: A nice little compression boulder adjacent to the railroad tracks. Sit Start with feet on big ledge and hands squeezing the right and left areate.  Make a hard move or two and then find the easiest way up.
content.location: Along railroad tracks just north of the Birthday Rocks area.

climbs.name: Cake Knife
climbs.fa: Ian CB and Anna Boatman probably

content.description: From a crouch, with a good full pad sidepull for the right and left on a good slopey spot near the base of the arete, climb the technical and tricky arete. Gain better holds up high, mantle, and the easiest way off is to down climb left.  We both thought this was quite fun.
content.protection: A few pads and a spot, the landing has a slight downhill pitch.
content.location: Just on the right side of the Railroad amphitheater at the base of the cliff.  20 feet right of the boulder problem, Grand Central.

content.description: Despite the short approach and being just up from the railroad tracks this area feels secluded.  Good place to go when it's damp as it gets afternoon sun and a nice breeze.
